</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PROCEDURES followed by the London Stock Exchange when it delists companies
do not need to be referred to the European Court of Justice, the Court of
Appeal in London has ruled.
The ruling overturns a High Court decision in July under which the
Exchange's interpretation of the EC's 1979 admissions directive was to have
been referred to the European court. This followed an appeal by shareholders
in Titaghur, a Scottish-based jute company.
