FT  16 OCT 92 / International Company News: Metra improves at eight-month
stage
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
METRA, the Finnish industrial group, reported yesterday a FM56m (Dollars
12.1m) loss for the first eight months of the year, a marked improvement on
the FM201m deficit suffered for the same period of 1991.
The group expects to make a profit for the whole of the year, compared with
a FM203m loss for the last financial year.
Net sales for the first eight months were Fm3.676bn, 18 per cent down from
the FM4.460bn recorded on the same period of 1991 as a result of recent
divestments. Metra added that sales were expected to reach around FM10bn for
the full year.
Metra said its sanitary equipment division (Sanitec) had seen a weakening in
profits, and net sales had not marched expectations, mainly due to
industrial disruption last summer in Germany.
The group said profits for the full year in its security division were
expected to improve slightly, but still remain unsatisfactory for the year.
Its steel operations and caravan division made a loss in the period.
