FT  16 OCT 92 / International Company News: Lockheed profit holds steady
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LOCKHEED, the US defence group, yesterday reported net earnings of Dollars
86m, or Dollars 1.40 a share, in the third quarter, compared with Dollars
81m, or Dollars 1.28, in the same period of 1991, writes Martin Dickson.
Mr Daniel Tellep, chairman, attributed the increase mainly to higher
programme profits in the aeronautical and electronics sectors. Sales were
Dollars 2.5bn, against Dollars 2.4bn.
Nine-months earnings totalled Dollars 229m, or Dollars 3.69 a share, on
sales of Dollars 7.2bn, up from earnings of Dollars 205m or Dollars 3.23 on
sales of Dollars 7.1bn.
