<HEADLINE>
FT  16 OCT 92 / UK Company News: Tudor moving into profit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Tudor, a tiles and crystal glassware company, recorded a pre-tax loss of
Pounds 117,000, after a Pounds 59,000 exceptional charge in the six months
to June 30. That followed the Pounds 71,000 deficit in the second half of
1991, when the final dividend was passed. The company was now said to be
profitable.
There is no interim dividend, against 0.5p paid from a profit of Pounds
94,000. Sales in the half year came to Pounds 7.8m (Pounds 6.42m). Losses
per share were 1.06p (earnings 1.24p).
